CareerOS Capstone — Execution Master File (P1 → P12)

Use this in any new chat to continue from the exact checkpoint.
This file combines your P1→P7 summary + our P8→P12 build + a full demo proof sequence with exact output locations and verification commands.

0) System goal (what we’re building)

CareerOS is an evidence-grounded, agentic career workflow that takes:

candidate intake + resume evidence

multiple job posts

…and produces:

explainable matching + ranking

job-specific application package artifacts

guardrails that block unsupported claims

exports (DOCX/PDF)

apply tracking ledger + analytics funnel

follow-up action queue + message drafts

one-click orchestration runner (agent-ready spine)

We built Phase 0 as a deterministic, versioned artifact pipeline (P1–P12) first, then we’ll layer agentic orchestration (L2/L3/L4) + MLflow/DVC afterward.

1) No-confusion mapping rule

P# = pipeline stages (implementation build order)

Arch L# = architecture responsibility layers (from your diagram)

A pipeline stage can map to multiple architecture layers.

2) Repo/runtime state (what is already working now)

✅ Python venv working
✅ FastAPI backend runs via Uvicorn
✅ Streamlit UI runs and calls backend
✅ Artifacts persist to disk under outputs/ and exports/
✅ outputs/ is gitignored
✅ pytest is used for unit tests
✅ Guardrails fixed to avoid false positives (no “thank/team/hiring” blocks)
✅ Export deps installed: python-docx, reportlab
✅ Dashboard deps installed: pandas
✅ UI uses api_url = os.getenv("CAREEROS_API_URL", "http://127.0.0.1:8000")

3) Pipeline layers summary (P1 → P12)
P1 — Intake Bundle (User preferences → IntakeBundle artifact)

Purpose: capture targeting constraints (roles/location/salary/work auth/remote) as a stable “contract”.
Belongs to Arch: L1 Entry (UI/API).
Inputs: Streamlit form fields.
Output artifact:

outputs/intake/intake_bundle_v1_<timestamp>.json
Verified: Streamlit button creates file; path shown; file exists.

P2 — Resume Parsing (Resume text → EvidenceProfile artifact)

Purpose: build the “truth source” for what can be claimed.
Belongs to Arch: L4 Agent behavior + supports L9 governance.
Inputs: resume text (paste).
Processing (Phase 0): deterministic extraction into skills/titles/domains.
Output artifact:

outputs/profile/profile_v1_<timestamp>.json
Verified: file exists; skills populated.

P3 — Job Ingestion (Job text → JobPost artifact)

Purpose: normalize job descriptions for matching/ranking.
Belongs to Arch: L4 Agent behavior.
Inputs: job description text (paste).
Processing: deterministic keyword extraction.
Output artifact:

outputs/jobs/job_post_v1_<timestamp>.json
Verified: multiple job posts ingested and saved.

P4 — Matching (EvidenceProfile + JobPost → MatchResult artifact)

Purpose: explainably compute overlap/missing and score (0–100).
Belongs to Arch: L3 Manager + L4 Agent.
Inputs: latest profile (P2), one job post (P3).
Processing: set compare + coverage score + rationale.
Output artifact:

outputs/matching/match_result_v1_<timestamp>.json
Verified: score + overlap/missing returned and saved.

P5 — Ranking (All jobs → RankedShortlist artifact)

Purpose: choose Top-N jobs with reasons (decision output).
Belongs to Arch: L3 Manager (Job Ops).
Inputs: latest profile + all jobs.
Processing: compute P4 per job, sort by score.
Output artifact:

outputs/ranking/shortlist_v1_<timestamp>.json
Verified: Top-3 shortlist returned with scores, overlap, missing, reasons.

P6 — Generation (Shortlist + Evidence → ApplicationPackage artifact)

Purpose: create job-specific deliverables grounded in overlap skills.
Belongs to Arch: L4 Agent behavior; later L8 Models/Memory.
Inputs: shortlist + profile + referenced job.
Processing (Phase 0): deterministic bullet generation + safe cover letter + QA stubs.
Output artifact:

exports/packages/application_package_v1_<jobhint>_<timestamp>.json
Verified: package file exists with bullets + cover letter + QA stubs.

P7 — Guardrails (Validate package → ValidationReport artifact)

Purpose: prove governance: block unsupported claims (MVP requirement).
Belongs to Arch: L9 Governance/Ops + L5 Human Gates.
Inputs: profile (P2) + package (P6).
Processing (Final Phase 0 rule GR001):

only blocks when known tool/tech terms appear that are NOT in EvidenceProfile.skills

avoids false blocks from common words
Output artifact:

outputs/guardrails/validation_report_v1_<timestamp>.json
Verified: pass/blocked works; Snowflake blocks; normal prose doesn’t.

P8 — Export + Apply Tracking (Validated Package → DOCX/PDF + lifecycle ledger)

Purpose: produce submit-ready artifacts + track each application’s lifecycle.
Belongs to Arch: L6 Execution Ops + L9 Governance.
Inputs: package + validation report (must pass).
Processing:

gate export if blocked

export docx/pdf

write/append record to tracking ledger

allow status updates (submitted/interview/offer/etc.)
Outputs:

exports/submissions/<application_id>_<job_hint>/application_package.docx

exports/submissions/<application_id>_<job_hint>/application_package.pdf

outputs/apply_tracking/applications_v1.jsonl
Verified: exports created + status updated to submitted.

P9 — Analytics Dashboard (Tracking ledger → funnel + list + drill-down)

Purpose: product-level observability for apply ops funnel.
Belongs to Arch: L7 Observability + supports L6/L9.
Inputs: applications ledger JSONL.
Outputs:

API:

GET /applications/metrics

GET /applications/list?status=&limit=

GET /applications/{application_id}

UI: metrics + filtered DataFrame + drill-down
Verified: filter works; table renders; drill-down works.

P10 — Next Actions (Ledger → follow-up action queue)

Purpose: deterministic ops automation (what to do next).
Belongs to Arch: L6 + L7 + L9.
Inputs: applications ledger.
Rules: follow_up, prepare_interview, update_status, close_loop.
Output artifact:

outputs/followups/followups_v1.json
API/UI: generate + load latest actions.
Verified: actions generated tied to application_id; test exists.

P11 — Notification Drafts (Action queue → email/linkedin drafts)

Purpose: generate ready-to-copy communications (Phase 0 = no sending).
Belongs to Arch: L6 + L7 + L9; later L5 approval.
Inputs: followups queue + applications ledger.
Output artifact:

outputs/notifications/drafts_v1.json
API/UI: build drafts + load drafts + open by draft_id.
Verified: drafts generated; follow_up yields email + LinkedIn drafts; test exists.

P12 — Orchestration Runner (One-click workflow: P6→P7→P8→P10→P11)

Purpose: agent-ready workflow spine (Director behavior in Phase 0).
Belongs to Arch: L3 Manager + L6 + L9 (interfaces with L4 later).
Inputs: profile_path, job_path, overlap_skills, tracking_path.
Processing: runs sequentially with strict gating:

if P7 blocked → stop; no exports/actions/drafts

if pass → completes downstream steps
Output: run JSON summary (run_id, steps, artifact paths).
Verified: block stops; pass completes.

4) How to run the whole system (API + UI + tests)
Install deps (if needed)
source .venv/bin/activate
python -m pip install -U pip
python -m pip install pytest pandas python-docx reportlab

Run tests (proof)
PYTHONPATH=src pytest -q

Run API
PYTHONPATH=src uvicorn apps.api.main:app --reload --port 8000

Run UI
CAREEROS_API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8000 streamlit run apps/ui/Home.py

5) Demo proof sequence (P1 → P12) — two runs: PASS + BLOCK
A) PASS run (happy path: full flow succeeds)

In Streamlit:

P1 Create Intake Bundle → show returned path

P2 Build Profile (paste resume) → show profile path

P3 Ingest 2–3 Jobs (paste job texts) → show job paths

P4 Run Matching (for at least one job) → show match_result path + overlap/missing

P5 Run Ranking → show shortlist path + ordered jobs

P6 Generate Package (Top-1) → show application_package path

P7 Validate → show validation report path with status: pass

P8 Export → show docx/pdf paths + application_id; confirm created on disk

P9 Dashboard → show funnel metrics + list filtered by submitted; drill-down by application_id

P10 Generate Next Actions → show followups path + actions table

P11 Build Drafts → show drafts path + open a draft_id

P12 Orchestrator (optional in PASS demo) → show status=ok and step outputs

PASS proof to screenshot:

P7 report status: pass

P8 docx/pdf exported folder

P9 funnel + submitted row

P10 actions table

P11 draft opened with body text

B) BLOCK run (governance proof: unsupported claim stops everything)

Generate package (P6)

Inject unsupported tool term (example: Snowflake) into package text OR ensure job/overlap forces the mention

Run P7 Validate

Expected:

P7 status: blocked

report includes unsupported_terms: ["snowflake"]

P8 export should not proceed

P12 orchestrator should stop at P7 and return blocked

BLOCK proof to screenshot:

validation report showing blocked + unsupported_terms

confirm no new exports/submissions/<new_id> folder created after block attempt

6) How to verify outputs on disk (quick commands)
Latest profile (P2)
ls -lt outputs/profile | head

Latest jobs (P3)
ls -lt outputs/jobs | head

Latest match result (P4)
ls -lt outputs/matching | head

Latest shortlist (P5)
ls -lt outputs/ranking | head

Latest package (P6)
ls -lt exports/packages | head

Latest validation report (P7)
ls -lt outputs/guardrails | head

Latest submissions (P8)
ls -lt exports/submissions | head

Tracking ledger (P8)
tail -n 3 outputs/apply_tracking/applications_v1.jsonl

Followups queue (P10)
cat outputs/followups/followups_v1.json | head -n 80

Drafts bundle (P11)
cat outputs/notifications/drafts_v1.json | head -n 80

7) Where to see “logs”

You mentioned structured logs exist at:

logs/careeros.jsonl

To show latest log events:

tail -n 30 logs/careeros.jsonl


